# License — Source Code (MIT)

## Scope of this license

This MIT License applies **only to the source code committed to this repository** — that is, the software files that make up The Drake Display engine and tooling (for example: `.py`, `.js`, `.jsx`, `.ts`, `.html`, `.css`, and build/configuration files), together with the inline code documentation bundled inside them (docstrings and code comments).

**This license does NOT apply to:**

- **Documentation and research content** (standalone Markdown research documents, specifications, plans, the data-source catalog, glossary, and project-management prose). Those are licensed separately under **Creative Commons Attribution 4.0** — see `LICENSE-CONTENT`.
- **Creative and narrative fiction** — any story prose, the novel manuscript, its outlines, and narrative worldbuilding text — which is **reserved, All Rights Reserved by the author**, whether or not any fragment appears in this repository. It is not licensed under MIT or CC.
- **Third-party materials** — astronomical data, catalogs, and external software libraries the project consumes or depends on. These remain governed by **their own original licenses and terms**; nothing here relicenses them.
- **The project name, branding, and any trademarks.**
- **Anything not committed to this repository** — including any files on the author's personal devices, private or unpublished drafts, notes, and any material outside this repository. Such material is expressly **not** covered by this license.

Where the standard MIT text below refers to "the Software" and its "associated documentation files," that phrase is to be read as the source code in this repository and its bundled inline documentation only, consistent with the scope above.

